  "prompt": "Is six hours of sleep enough for a 10-year-old?",
  "response": "No, six hours of sleep is generally not enough for a 10-year-old. The American Academy of Sleep Medicine recommends that children aged 6 to 12 years should get about 9 to 12 hours of sleep each night for optimal health, growth, and development. Insufficient sleep can lead to various issues, including difficulties with concentration, mood changes, and impacts on overall health. If a child is consistently getting less than the recommended amount of sleep, it may be beneficial to assess their sleep habits and consider adjustments.",
